{
  "name": "refactor-the-phase-config-20260414-0017",
  "idea": "Refactor the phase config mode-switching architecture to eliminate the dual-writer problem. Currently when generationTypeMode changes (I2V <-> VACE), two mechanisms compete to set phaseConfig: (1) rebuildPhaseConfig called imperatively from handlers, and (2) usePresetAutoSelect firing on next render. This creates race conditions and allows selectedPhasePresetId and phaseConfig to get out of sync. The fix: make handleGenerationTypeModeChange atomically set mode + preset ID + phaseConfig in a single updateFields call using the builtin preset config (with user loras merged in). Remove the redundant rebuildPhaseConfig call from mode switching. Restrict usePresetAutoSelect to only handle initial mount / shot navigation, not mode changes already handled by the explicit handler. Key files: src/tools/travel-between-images/hooks/settings/useVideoTravelSettingsHandlers.ts, src/tools/travel-between-images/hooks/settings/usePresetAutoSelect.ts, src/tools/travel-between-images/components/ShotEditor/services/generateVideo/modelPhase.ts, src/shared/types/phaseConfig.ts",
